HEADWORD: Tigers-foot
<hw>Ti"ger's-foot`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A name given to some species of morning-glory (<gen>Ipomoea</gen>)
having the leaves lobed in pedate fashion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

